ğŸ”¹ What is Git?

Git is a version control system used to track changes in code/files.
It helps developers save history, work safely, and roll back mistakes.

ğŸ”¹ Why Git is Used?

Track code changes

Work in teams without overwriting code

Create multiple versions (branches)

Recover old code if something breaks

ğŸ”¹ What is GitHub?

GitHub is a cloud platform that hosts Git repositories online.
It allows teams to store, share, collaborate, and manage code remotely.

ğŸ”¹ Git vs GitHub (Very Important)
Git	GitHub
Tool	Platform
Works locally	Works online
Tracks versions	Hosts repositories
No internet required	Internet required


ğŸ”¹ Setup

git --version â†’ Check Git version

git config --global user.name "name" â†’ Set username

git config --global user.email "email" â†’ Set email

git config --list â†’ View config

ğŸ“ Repo

git init â†’ Initialize repo

git clone URL â†’ Clone GitHub repo

ğŸ“„ Status & Stage

git status â†’ Repo status

git add file â†’ Stage file

git add . â†’ Stage all

git restore --staged file â†’ Unstage

ğŸ’¾ Commit

git commit -m "msg" â†’ Commit changes

git commit --amend â†’ Edit last commit

git log â†’ Commit history

git log --oneline â†’ Short history

ğŸŒ¿ Branch

git branch â†’ List branches

git branch name â†’ Create branch

git checkout name â†’ Switch branch

git checkout -b name â†’ Create + switch

git branch -d name â†’ Delete branch

ğŸ”€ Merge / Rebase

git merge branch â†’ Merge branch

git rebase main â†’ Rebase branch

ğŸŒ Remote (GitHub)

git remote add origin URL â†’ Add remote

git remote -v â†’ View remote

git push origin main â†’ Push code

git push -u origin main â†’ First push

git pull origin main â†’ Pull updates

git fetch â†’ Fetch only

ğŸ” Undo / Reset

git restore file â†’ Undo file changes

git reset --soft HEAD~1 â†’ Undo commit (keep changes)

git reset --hard HEAD~1 â†’ Undo commit (delete changes)

git revert commitID â†’ Safe undo

ğŸ” Diff / Inspect

git diff â†’ Unstaged diff

git diff --staged â†’ Staged diff

git show commitID â†’ Commit details

ğŸ· Tags

git tag v1.0 â†’ Create tag

git push origin v1.0 â†’ Push tag

ğŸ“¦ Stash

git stash â†’ Save work

git stash list â†’ View stash

git stash apply â†’ Restore stash

ğŸ§¹ Cleanup

git clean -f â†’ Remove untracked files

ğŸ” GitHub SSH

ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 â†’ Generate SSH key

ssh -T git@github.com â†’ Test GitHub access
